1)chk_xmltexts.php lists up translatable texts 
  from xml files under target path.
  You can specify the path in chk_var.php .
  
2)chk_translations.php lists up translation candidates 
  from Babel database.
  Babel database requires the "latin1" encoding,
  not "UTF-8". And You can specify user id in chk_var.php .

3-1)
  upd_atf_xmls.php replaces texts in xml files
  under "convert" directory for org.eclipse.atf.doc .

3-2)
  upd_pdt_xmls.php replaces texts
  for org.eclipse.php.help .
  (also some of com.zend.php.help )

3-3)
  upd_platform_xmls.php replaces some of texts
  for org.eclipse.platform.doc.user .
  (under making)
  
3-4)
  upd_svn_xmls.php  replaces texts
  for org.eclipse.team.svn.help .

Where you can take Babel data dump?
  see Babel Server weekly mysqldump on
  http://www.eclipse.org/babel/downloads.php

Thanks!

